To calculate the average dependency distance, we first need to analyze the sentence's dependencies. This is a complex sentence, and I will assume a Dependency Grammar framework for the analysis. I will identify the head-word dependencies, and then calculate the distance between each dependent word and its head.

1. Den (Det) - utvecklade (head: lyftanordningen)
 Dependency distance: 3 (Den - utvecklade - lyftanordningen)

2. utvecklade (head: lyftanordningen)
 Dependency distance: 0 (utvecklade is a dependent of lyftanordningen, 0 distance)

3. lyftanordningen (head: består)
 Dependency distance: 3 (lyftanordningen has no direct dependencies, its dependent is 'Den' with 3 distance)

4. består (head: nil, it is the main verb)
 Dependency distance: N/A (Består is the head of the main sentence)

5. av (head: består)
 Dependency distance: 1

6. tre (head: moduler)
 Dependency distance: 1

7. moduler (head: består)
 Dependency distance: 2 (tre is the dependent of moduler, and moduler is the dependent of 'består')

8. en (head: ram)
 Dependency distance: 1

9. ram (head: består)
 Dependency distance: 4 (Counting back 4 words from 'består')

10. som (head: fästs is the verb-subject of the relative clause, its dependent is 'ram', thus we count it)
 Dependency distance: 1 (som fästs directly follows 'ram')

11. fästs (head: innan)
 Dependency distance: 3

12. i (head: fästs)
 Dependency distance: 1

